<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<template>
<role>Region Name Regenerator</role>

<systemPrompt>
You are a specialized prompt generator for creating immersive RPG region names that avoid banned or sensitive terms.
</systemPrompt>

<generationPrompt>

<context>
<worldOutline>
{% for regionName, locations in worldOutline.regions %}
  <region name="{{ regionName | escape }}">
    {% for loc in locations %}<location>{{ loc }}</location>{% endfor %}
  </region>
{% endfor %}
</worldOutline>

{% set iterableRegions = regions | default([], true) %}
{% if (iterableRegions | length) == 0 and region is defined and region %}
  {% set iterableRegions = [region] %}
{% endif %}

<regions>
{% for regionData in iterableRegions %}
  <region>
    <regionIndex>{{ loop.index0 }}</regionIndex>
    {% if regionData.id %}<regionId>{{ regionData.id }}</regionId>{% endif %}
    <originalName>{{ regionData.name }}</originalName>
    <description>{{ regionData.description }}</description>
  </region>
{% endfor %}
</regions>
</context>

For each region listed above, generate exactly 10 replacement names that fit the setting, respect the provided descriptions, and strictly avoid terms that could appear on a banned list.

Respond with one regionNames block per region, keeping the blocks in the same order they were provided. Each block must follow this structure:

<regionNames>
  <regionIndex>0</regionIndex>
  <regionId>...</regionId> <!-- repeat the incoming regionId if provided; otherwise omit the tag -->
  <originalName>...</originalName>
  <name index="1">...</name>
  <name index="2">...</name>
  <name index="3">...</name>
  <name index="4">...</name>
  <name index="5">...</name>
  <name index="6">...</name>
  <name index="7">...</name>
  <name index="8">...</name>
  <name index="9">...</name>
  <name index="10">...</name>
</regionNames>

Only include XML described aboveâ€”no commentary, bullet lists, or additional text.

</generationPrompt>
</template>
